In this example, we use `document.querySelector()` to find the `<textarea>` element based on its `data-testid` attribute. We then add an event listener to the element that listens for changes in its input using the `input` event. When the user types something, we send the current value of the `<textarea>` to a Socket.IO server using the `socket.emit()` method.

Note that in order to use Socket.IO, you will need to include the Socket.IO client library in your extension

